body:
@aoen the beta is a branch: v1-8-test . It tracks master currently although manually (so it allows for cherry picking if necessary, but I rather avoid it for non stable). In principle I am positive that anyone can merge from master to this branch, although with the caveat that large changes should be avoided. I would prefer bug fixes that don't change a contract go in easily (eg. by anyone). Fixes that do change o contract or new features left to the release manager or discussed on the mailing list. In other words this branch is a little bit more controlled/managed

When we hit RC I will branch off v1-8-stable, which is quite fixed and only signed off patches should enter. The version in v1-8-test will then change to 1.8.1dev0 (or maybe alpha0) and master will change to 1.9.0dev0.

Doe that make sense?

@bolkedebruin, Sure, I know you are quite busy with 1.8 release, Thanks for that as well.
please take a look at your convenience.

Yes, I am using ssh heavily in my workflow on staging right now, and will be on prod next week.
